-=> Quoting Bruce Schneier to All <=-

BS> If you take a data file and compress it using Huffman coding
BS> techniques, you get something that looks random.  Make the coding table
BS> the key, and the compressed text is now ciphertext.  Although there is
BS> no reason to believe that this is in any secure, I know of no one who
BS> has any idea how to cryptanalyze it.

BS> I have heard a lot of folklore on this topic; does anyone know of any
BS> actual reserach results?

What about applying a homophonic channel in between the model and the
coder?  This should make the output void of the high order message
statisitics.

